## Final Capstone: Debug a Complete Webpage

Below is a complete small business landing page — HTML, CSS, and JavaScript all in one file. It looks like a real page a contractor might deliver or that AI might generate.

But it has **5 intentional bugs** — problems that span HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Your job is to read the code, understand what each section does, and find the issues.

Take your time. Read it section by section, just like you have practiced throughout this course.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
  <title>Greenleaf Landscaping</title>
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333; }

    /* Navigation */
    .nav { background: #2d5016; padding: 16px 24px; display: flex;
           justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
    .nav a { color: white; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 20px; }
    .nav .logo { font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; color: white; }
    .mobile-menu { display: none; cursor: pointer; color: white;
                   font-size: 24px; background: none; border: none; }

    /* Hero Section */
    .hero { background: #4a7c23; color: white; text-align: center;
            padding: 80px 24px; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 42px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .hero p { font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .hero .cta { background: white; color: #2d5016; padding: 14px 32px;
                 border: none; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 16px;
                 cursor: pointer; }

    /* Features */
    .features { padding: 60px 24px; display: flex; gap: 32px;
                justify-content: center; }
    .feature-card { text-align: center; max-width: 280px; }
    .feature-card h3 { color: #2d5016; margin: 12px 0 8px; }

    /* Contact Form */
    .contact { background: #f5f5f5; padding: 60px 24px;
               text-align: center; }
    .contact h2 { margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .contact form { max-width: 400px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .contact input, .contact textarea {
      width: 100%; padding: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 14px; }
    .contact textarea { height: 120px; resize: vertical; }
    .contact button { background: #2d5016; color: white; padding: 12px 32px;
                      border: none; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 16px;
                      cursor: pointer; }
    div.contact button { background: #999; }

    /* Footer */
    footer { background: #1a1a1a; color: white; text-align: center;
             padding: 24px; font-size: 14px; }

    /* Responsive — missing mobile breakpoint */
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="nav">
    <span class="logo">Greenleaf Landscaping</span>
    <button class="mobile-menu" onclick="toggleMenu()">☰</button>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="#features">Services</a>
      <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      <a href="#about">About</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Transform Your Outdoor Space</h1>
    <p>Professional landscaping services for homes and businesses.</p>
    <button class="cta" onclick="scrollToSection('contact-form')">Get a Free Quote</button>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section class="features" id="features">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <img src="images/design-icon.png" width="64" height="64">
      <h3>Custom Design</h3>
      <p>Tailored landscape plans that match your vision and budget.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <img src="images/maintenance-icon.png" width="64" height="64" alt="Maintenance icon">
      <h3>Maintenance</h3>
      <p>Weekly and monthly care to keep your property looking its best.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <img src="images/irrigation-icon.png" width="64" height="64" alt="Irrigation icon">
      <h3>Irrigation</h3>
      <p>Smart watering systems that save water and keep your lawn green.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Form -->
  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <h2>Request a Free Quote</h2>
    <form id="contact-form">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Your Name" required>
      <input type="text" placeholder="Your Email" required>
      <textarea placeholder="Tell us about your project"></textarea>
      <button type="submit">Send Request</button>
    </form>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 Greenleaf Landscaping. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>

  <script>
    // Mobile menu toggle
    function toggleMenu() {
      const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
      navLinks.classList.toggle('active');
    }

    // Scroll to section
    function scrollToSection(sectionId) {
      const section = document.querySelector('#' + sectionId);
      section.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
    }

    // Form validation
    document.querySelector('#contact-form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const name = this.querySelector('input[placeholder="Your Name"]').value;
      const email = this.querySelector('input[placeholder="Your Email"]').value;

      if (name.length > 0 || email.length > 0) {
        alert('Thank you! We will be in touch soon.');
        this.reset();
      } else {
        alert('Please fill in all required fields.');
      }
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
```

## The 5 Bugs

Before we quiz you, here is a summary of the areas to examine:

1. **Accessibility** — Check the `<img>` tags. Are they all properly accessible?
2. **CSS specificity** — Look at the contact section's submit button styling. Is the green color actually being applied?
3. **JavaScript logic** — Read the form validation carefully. Does the condition actually require *both* fields to be filled in?
4. **JavaScript selector** — The "Get a Free Quote" button calls `scrollToSection('contact-form')`. Does that ID exist on the section the user expects to scroll to?
5. **Responsive design** — Check the viewport meta tag and look for media queries. Is this page ready for mobile screens?

